column5: Anybody know anything about the health of the Scugog walleye population since the fishery was closed?
I have not heard a thing, not even accidentally caught posts or PM's from friends/folks in the area while crappie or perch fishing.
The walleye fishery has been closed for a while now. I hope the population is recovering.  If not, are they stocking?
I was there musky fishing a year ago and happened into a 6 lber and a 7 lber. So strap on a big musky lure and see what happens!
Good sign. Not a good indicator of recruitment though.
